Workout Tracker App
A simple workout tracker app built using Node.js, HTML, and CSS. This app allows you to track your workout routines for various muscle groups and stores the data in a JSON file.

Features
Add workout plans for different muscle groups (e.g., Chest, Back, Legs).
View existing workout plans.
Modify or delete workout plans.
Data stored in workout.json file.
Technologies Used
Frontend: HTML, CSS
Backend: Node.js
Data Storage: Local JSON file (workout.json)
Prerequisites
Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed on your system:

Node.js (version 14.x or higher)
npm (Node Package Manager)
Getting Started
Follow these steps to get the app running locally on your machine:

1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/workout-tracker-app.git

2. Navigate into the project directory
cd workout-tracker-app

3. Install dependencies
npm install

4. Start the server
node server.js

The server should now be running on http://localhost:3000.

### File Structure ###

workout-tracker-app/
│
├── server.js            # Node.js server for handling routes
├── workout.json         # JSON file storing workout plans
├── public/              # Contains static assets (HTML, CSS, images)
│   ├── index.html       # Main HTML page
│   └── styles.css       # Styles for the app
└── README.md            # Project documentation (this file)

API Endpoints
1. GET /workouts/:muscleGroup
Fetch workout plans for a specific muscle group.

2. POST /workouts/:muscleGroup
Add a new workout plan for a specific muscle group.

3. DELETE /workouts/:muscleGroup/:id
Delete a workout plan from a specific muscle group.

Troubleshooting
Common Errors:
Error reading workout data:

Ensure that the workout.json file exists and is accessible by the server.
Make sure the file is valid in JSON format.
"500 Internal Server Error":

This could be related to file read/write issues. Could you make sure the workout.json file has the proper read/write permissions?

Contributing
If you'd like to contribute to this project, feel free to fork the repository, make improvements, and submit a pull request!

P.S. look at the file structure and I have tried my best to add it in the same order just rearrange it if something goes wrong.
